        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:02PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 602 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of House, or 28 miles northeast of Fort Sumner, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clovis, Texico, Melrose, Grady, House, Ranchvale, Saint Vrain,
Cannon Air Force Base, Broadview and Ragland.

This includes Highway 60 between Mile Markers 358 and 397.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
